{
  "texts": [
    "We are using capital letters only as a reminder that the possibilities in F ℘ are sets of worlds.",
    "For negative results on internal adjointness and the finite existence lemma in the context of quantified modal logic, seeHarrison-Trainor 2019.",
    "Rumfitt goes up rather than down for refinements (writing '•' for join), but we maintain our convention from Remark 2.2.",
    "Note that the proof of Theorem 7.13 in § 7.3 shows how to obtain completeness of a normal modal logic L with respect to an atomless and functional full possibility frame without assuming that L itself has internal adjointness, by taking a detour through the minimal tense extension of L, which always has internal adjointness."
  ]
}